As we approach our next National Adoption Weekend event we wanted to share this sweet adoption story that was sent to us!
Phoebe was adopted from a PetSmart in Robinson, PA back in 2010. According to her owner, Suzanne, she was extremely scared, shy, and would not come to the front of her cage for Suzanne to meet her. Suzanne knew that once she earned Phoebe's trust and love they'd both be happy about the adoption. According to Suzanne, it didnâ€™t take very long after getting her home for her to warm up to her new family.
8 years later she is the sweetest, most loving, loyal pet. Phoebe just needed her forever home and someone to love her.

We are pleased to announce that we have a new program that partners with local and southern California TNR groups to help orphaned kittens by socializing them and finding loving homes. Big Red is one of those kittens. He is now 10 months old. He was turned into a local shelter and was going to be euthanized for being feral at only 4 months old. He is anything but. He loves kids, cats and gets along with dogs. His adoption fee is $75. He's neutered, chipped and vaccinated.
